"n.厌食症 【英】 n. 厌食症( an eating disorder, aversion to food) 【记】 an+orex(胃口)+ia→ 无胃口的病 n. (因疾病而起的)厌食症 【例】anorexia nervosa 神经性食欲缺乏 【记】1)an非, 无, orex = orexis食欲, ia病－无食欲的病－厌食症2)a一个, no不, re拼: 热, xia病－一个不热的病－厌食症很easy! 因为不吃食物就不能摄入卡路里, 就不能产生热量. 【记】an不 + oral(口，嘴)+音：下→嘴里吃不下 【相关】dyslexia(阅读障碍) anorexia (n.)  1590s, ""lack of appetite,"" Modern Latin, from Greek anorexia, from an-, privative prefix, ""without"" (see an- (1)) + orexis ""appetite, desire,"" from oregein ""to desire, stretch out"" (cognate with Latin regere ""to keep straight, guide, rule;"" see regal). In current use, often short for anorexia nervosa."
